onic oscillators, and an interacting scalar\nQFT. Finally, we argue that the logarithm of the Feynman-Vernon influence\nfunctional is the correct analog of the Wilsonian effective action for this\nproblem.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Tue, 9 Dec 2014 22:54:51 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 8 Feb 2016 20:00:04 GMT"},{"version":"v3","created":"Fri, 8 Jun 2018 17:37:19 GMT"},{"version":"v4","created":"Mon, 11 Jun 2018 20:41:18 GMT"}],"update_date":"2018-08-01"}
