for the decelerating jet\nmodel or particle cascade model. We also found that the peak value of $T_{\\rm\n0}\\approx3.4\\times10^{10}$ K is close to the equipartition temperature,\nimplying that the VLBI cores observable at 2-86 GHz may be representing jet\nregions where the magnetic field energy dominates the total energy in jets.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 10 Dec 2014 08:16:43 GMT"}],"update_date":"2015-06-23"}
